resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The blue character has training shoes and five Olympic rings on its body.\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2968, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 Created by John Ryan, DESIGNefx.\", \"from\": 2970, \"to\": 3004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2983, \"end\": 2992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_P._Ryan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 3.2928797293656635e-13, \"text\": \"John Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_P._Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_P._Ryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 Izzy, initially called \\\"Whatizit\\\" (later \\\"Whatizhee\\\"), faced criticism for its ambiguous form and underwent several redesigns.\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sydney 2000  PHOTO: OLYMPICS.COM  \\u2022 Syd, a platypus, Olly, a kookaburra, and Millie, an echidna, represent Australia's environment and heritage.\", \"from\": 3136, \"to\": 3280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3243, \"end\": 3252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999736247, \"rank\": 1.4459395815293973e-11, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 Created by Matthew Hatton.\", \"from\": 3282, \"to\": 3310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3295, \"end\": 3309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hatton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Hatton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hatton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hatton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 Syd is a reference to Sydney, Olly to Olympics and Millie to the new millennium.\", \"from