scot  PHOTO: OLYMPICS.COM  \\u2022 A character with traditional and futuristic elements, symbolising a fusion of tradition and innovation.\", \"from\": 5007, \"to\": 5152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5007, \"end\": 5012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.937968462509048, \"rank\": 0.0661339266412632, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 Created by Ryo Taniguchi.\", \"from\": 5154, \"to\": 5181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5171, \"end\": 5180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maybach_Taniguchi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Taniguchi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maybach_Taniguchi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maybach_Taniguchi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 The name Miraitowa combines the Japanese words \\\"mirai\\\" (future) and \\\"towa\\\" (eternity).\", \"from\": 5183, \"to\": 5271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5194, \"end\": 5203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miraitowa_and_Someity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Miraitowa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miraitowa_and_Someity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miraitowa_and_Someity\"}, {\"begin\": 5217, \"end\": 5225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9999999734873203, \"rank\": 2.639502637259277e-08, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a blue chequered outfit, the character wears a stylised samurai-style helmet.\", \"from\": 5272, \"to\": 5354, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 The mascot blends traditional and futuristic styles, symbolising \\\"innovation from harmony\\\", with its forehead featuring the Tokyo 2020 Games emblem - a chessboard motif of indigo-blue rectangles in three sizes.\", \"from\": 5356, \"to\": 5568, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: OLYMPICS.COM  \\u2022 Shaped like a Phrygian cap - a symbol of freedom in French history - Olympic Phryge appears in the French tricolour (blue, white and red).\", \"from\": 5570, \"to\": 5731, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5607, \"end\": 5619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phrygian cap\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 5645, \"end\": 5659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 Represents the power of sport to change lives and lead a revolution.\", \"from\": 5733, \"to\": 5803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 Created by Paris 2024 Design Team.\", \"from\": 5805, \"to\": 5841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 Motto is \\\"Alone we go faster, but together we go farther\\\".\", \"from\": 5843, \"to\": 5903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 Phrygian caps are widely recognised symbols in French culture, appearing in art, institutions and everyday objects.\", \"from\": 5905, \"to\": 6022, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5907, \"end\": 5915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.697544049741171e-21, \"text\": \"Phrygian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 5954, \"end\": 5968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2022 They also hold international significance as a symbol of liberty, used by freed slaves and on various emblems in North and South America.\", \"from\": 6024, \"to\": 6163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6149, \"end\": 6162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_America\", \"score\": 0.9999999998926796, \"rank\": 1.0062377813705993e-10, \"text\": \"South America\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_America\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cultural representation:Embody host country's culture, history and values.Festive atmosphere:Create a fun, celebratory and engaging environment.Appeal to youth:Connect with children and young people, inspiring future generations.Marketing:Enhance brand recognition, promote merchandise and generate revenue.Symbolism:Represent the Olympic spirit, values and ideals (excellence, friendship and respect).Legacy:Leave a lasting impression, becoming cherished collectibles and cultural symbols.Educational tool:Teach children about different cultures and the history of the Olympic Games.Unifying force:Bring people from diverse backgrounds together in a shared experience.Emotional connection:Evoke positive emotions, creating a sense of excitement and anticipation.Global ambassadors:Promote the host country and the Olympic movement on the world stage.\", \"from\": 6165, \"to\": 7016, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Source and illustrations:Olympics.com  Olympics 2024  Olympics  France  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 7018, \"to\": 7205, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7043, \"end\": 7055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.